Thousands of silver fish have died in Rodrigo de Freitas lake where Olympic rowing and canoeing events will be held in Rio de Janeiro in 2016 . 
  More than 37 tons of fish have been collected but there is an overwhelming stench . 
  City authorities and biologists have argued about the cause of the deaths . 
  Rio's environmental secretariat insists it is the result of a change in water temperature . 
 